body:
2007/5/3, sivasakthi :
> Hi Users,
>
> I have used following code,
>
> #!/usr/bin/perl
> use strict;
> use warnings;
> my $x=param("hhh");
> my $y=param(sss);
> my $z=param(ttt);
>


Mmmn,I think you would write them as,

use strict;
use warnings;
use CGI qw/:standard/;

my $x = param('hhh');
my $y = param('sss');
...

don't forget the quotation mark when passing arguments to a subroutine.

